    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Indianapolis Ind.</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 27, 1879.</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental">Mr. Charles Darwin.</seg>
                    <salute>Dear Sir.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Knowing your authority on the theory of evolution as relating to man, I take the liberty of of asking you if you will be so kind as to give me a list of books on the subject, such as a person desiring to cover the entire ground may need.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>By doing this you will greatly oblige | your very sincerely | Charles E. Ferguson</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">For CD’s reply, see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 28, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12630.xml">letter to C. E. Ferguson, 12 January 1880</ref>.
            </note>
        </div>
    
    </body>
